  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (c5fd67b 2024-01-15T00:23:11.184513736Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge init abc\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\n`forge init` fails when git global configs `user.name` and `user.email` are unset. Those settings are not necessary when initiating a git repo, and I do not want to set those global settings (with multiple accounts I want to minimize the chance of mixing things up, so I set those for each repo individually).",
